      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Carlotta Gall (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Gall, Carlotta</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bakter, Afghan state news agency, reports that Pres Hamid Karzai has appointed new electoral commission to replace Joint Election Management Board, which has been criticized for handling of October presidential elections (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>President Hamid Karzai bowed to pressure from his opponents and appointed a new electoral commission to prepare for parliamentary elections this year, the state news agency, Bakter, reported. The new commission of nine, drawn from all ethnic groups, will replace the Joint Election Management Board, criticized for its handling of the presidential elections in October.</p>
        <p>Carlotta Gall (NYT)</p>
      </block>
